17/04/2011
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- Justice Minister Ales Zalar and Serbian counterpart Snezana Malovic signed an extradition agreement Friday (April 15th) at Brdo pri Kranju. This marks the first such document Serbia has signed with an EU member. A second agreement covers legal aid in civil and criminal cases. After the ceremony, Malovic told the Tanjug news agency that the agreements will help strengthen bilateral co-operation in the fight against organised crime and corruption and will lead to direct co-operation between the judicial institutions of the two countries, including the establishment of joint investigative teams. Malovic and Zalar were attending a regional meeting on organised crime. (STA, Tanjug, Srna, Nezavisne Novine - 15/04/11)
